1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,000
Andy?

2
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:14,000
Attend the tale of Sweeney Todd, His skin was pale and his eye was odd.

3
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:19,000
Yes, he shaved the faces of gentlemen Who never thereafter were heard of again.

4
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:28,000
He trod a path that few have trod, It's Sweeney Todd, The demon barber of Fleet Street.

5
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Did you write this?

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,000
No.

7
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Who did?

8
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Steven Sondheim.

9
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Who is he?

10
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Swing your razor wide, Sweeney, hold it to the sky.

11
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Sweeney blows the blood of Elso Morlart.

12
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:49,000
What the hell is happening?

13
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:52,000
We're the cast of Sweeney Todd, The demon barber of Fleet Street.

14
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:55,000
We opened in a couple of weeks at the Loose Group Playhouse here in Scranton,

15
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,000
And today just doing a wee bit of viral marketing.

16
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Attend the tale of Sweeney Todd, He served a dark and avenging god.

17
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,000
What happens then?

18
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Well, that's the play, And he wouldn't want us to give it away.

19
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Sweeney Todd, The demon barber of Fleet Street.

20
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Wow!

21
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,000
Oh, that was amazing!

22
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:31,000
That was awesome!

23
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,000
I auditioned for this.

24
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,000
When did the cast list go up?

25
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Like a month ago.

26
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,000
Really?

27
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:40,000
They didn't call me.

28
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:43,000
Who am I playing?

29
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:45,000
Andy?

30
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:23,000
Two comps, for my lady and her Gabe.

31
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,000
It's closing night.

32
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:27,000
Tomorrow we have to give the theater over to the Scranton's Miss Fitness Pageant.

33
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,000
I am so excited, but I just need one.

34
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:31,000
Gabe can't come, sorry.

35
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,000
What?

36
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Yeah.

37
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,000
That's awful.

38
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Everyone's doing a Miss Psych guy.

39
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:38,000
Gabe is not coming, which is huge,

40
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:42,000
because my plan is to make Erin fall back in love with me tonight.

41
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:46,000
Women cannot resist a man singing show tunes.

42
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:51,000
It's so powerful, even a lot of men can't resist a man singing show tunes.

43
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,000
Oh, who else is going?

44
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Everyone.

45
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,000
Gabe seemed to think no one was going.

46
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:58,000
What kind of terrible rumor monger is Gabe?

47
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,000
He is woefully ill-informed, all right?

48
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Excuse me.

49
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,000
Okay, link, link, link, link, everybody.

50
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,000
You're all coming to my show tonight, right?

51
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,000
Andy, what time does it start?

52
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,000
8 p.m. sharp.

53
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,000
How long is it?

54
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,000
Hour 45.

55
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,000
I can't make it.

56
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:14,000
They say that no one can take your pride,

57
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:18,000
but the people who cast Andy's play, they took mine.

58
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Jim, Pam, you guys are in, right?

59
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Oh, we wanted to, but our sitter just fell through.

60
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,000
I'm really sorry.

61
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,000
Dwight?

62
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:27,000
No, thank you.

63
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:32,000
Last time I went to the theater, a man dressed as a cat sat on my lap.

64
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:36,000
It would mean so much to me if you came to my show tonight.

65
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,000
I can't, Andy.

66
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,000
It's too hard.

67
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:40,000
That's...

68
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,000
I put everything I had into that audition.

69
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,000
Do you understand that?

70
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,000
If it makes you feel any better,

71
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:48,000
no one who auditioned for the part of Sweeney Todd got that part.

72
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:50,000
They had to bring in a ringer.

73
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Well...

74
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,000
This guy's, like, world-class.

75
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,000
He should not feel bad.

76
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:58,000
I'm asking you, thespian to thespian,

77
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,000
will you please stop?

78
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,000
I'm asking you, thespian to thespian,

79
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:05,000
will you please be the bigger man and come to my show?

80
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:08,000
I wish I could, Andy, but I can't.

81
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:11,000
I have plans that night.

82
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:16,000
I'm going to see a friend in a play called Sweeney Todd.

83
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,000
You're that friend.

84
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:19,000
I'm going to see your play.

85
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:23,000
Nice!

86
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,000
And scene.

87
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:28,000
Listen, I would like you to take me to Andy's play tonight.

88
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Please, waste of time.

89
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,000
You know what?

90
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,000
Let's just knock this out right now.

91
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Disrobe.

92
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Angela?

93
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:36,000
Don't like her anymore.

94
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Not attracted to her anymore.

95
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:41,000
Just contractually obligated to make a baby with her.

96
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,000
Give me the punch card.

97
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,000
No.

98
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,000
If you want to punch the punch card,

99
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:46,000
you have to take me to the show.

100
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,000
That is not in the contract.

101
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:50,000
Well, there's a lot of gray area in that clause.

102
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,000
Do you want to remediate?

103
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,000
Right, fine.

104
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,000
I'll go to your little show.

105
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,000
But I'm not wearing a cape.

106
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,000
Thank you.

107
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:01,000
Dwight and I have a contractual agreement to procreate five times,

108
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,000
plain and simple.

109
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:06,000
And should he develop feelings for me?

110
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:10,000
Well, that would be permissible under item 7C clause 2.

111
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:13,000
So I would not object.

112
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:16,000
Hey, how are those salads?

113
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,000
It's my own fault.

114
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:20,000
My parents used to scramble to find babysitters

115
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,000
so they could take my little brother to do stuff.

116
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,000
I understand how hard it can be.

117
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:26,000
I just, tonight, I mean, if you could...

118
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,000
We'll keep looking.

119
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,000
Yes!

120
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,000
Really?

121
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,000
I mean, who knows?

122
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,000
Maybe I have a niece my family never told me about.

123
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,000
Oh my gosh, that would be amazing.

124
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,000
Yeah.

125
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,000
For a lot of reasons.

126
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,000
Yeah, I know.

127
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,000
Niche!

128
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,000
I need a lot of people tonight.

129
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,000
Big crowd.

130
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:44,000
You know, counting on that crowd dynamic to help Aaron love the show.

131
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,000
Like, when I go to a concert and there's 20,000 fans,

132
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,000
I have a great time.

133
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:52,000
But if I saw Justin Bieber alone at a museum,

134
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,000
I'd probably punch him in the face.

135
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,000
I'm not worried about Aaron seeing Andy's play alone.

136
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,000
She's already getting her actor fixed.

137
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,000
In the third grade, we did Sleepy Hollow.

138
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,000
I played Ichabod Crane.

139
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,000
They picked the play just so I could be in it.

140
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,000
Seventh grade, totally randomly, I played the same role.

141
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:08,000
Eleventh grade, I played Abraham Lincoln.

142
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:11,000
And in college, Ichabod Crane again.

143
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:16,000
I'll be there, but do not expect to stand in ovation.

144
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:20,000
I am sick of going to shows and feeling like I need to stand

145
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,000
when the show isn't that good.

146
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:24,000
You hear me, Steve Harvey?

147
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,000
We love culture, but Bob hates New York.

148
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,000
Too many...

149
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,000
Well, he just hates it.
